(181, NULL, 4, 'Information Technology Business Analyst', 'Airport Labs', 'Cluj-Napoca', 'HYBRID', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BUSINESS', 'Gradient Boosting', 1.0000, '[{\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 1}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Despre job\nAbout the role \nAirportLabs is providing a complete suite of products that drives efficiency in aviation. Our products and solutions help major airports, airlines, and ground handlers worldwide solve the hardest operational problems, improve efficiency, and develop the value of their services.\n\nWe are looking for a Business Analyst who is motivated to understand how airport operations work in practice and translate complex workflows into clear, actionable product requirements.\n\nThis is a hands-on, product-oriented role, working at the intersection of business and engineering. You will collaborate closely with users, product managers, and development teams to clarify needs, structure requirements, and support solution design all the way to production.\n\nIf you are comfortable navigating ambiguity, asking the right questions, and driving clarity across teams, this role could be a strong fit.\n\nKey facts to consider\n1500 - 2700 GBP gross/per month, depending on role fit and experience level\nYearly profit share and various performance and behavior-based bonuses\nRead more about our benefits here: https://www.airportlabs.com/careers#benefits \nIn-office or hybrid (partial office & partial remote)\nOffice location: Cluj-Napoca\nContract based on PFA or SRL with our UK entity\nPaid holidays\nInternational Exposure\n\nResponsibilities\nUnderstand and document the problem to be solved\nTranslate business requirements and needs into product solutions\nCoordinate with the product team members on the requirements clarification step and assist all the way to production release\nContribute to the development and improvement of the team practices and of the business requirements processes\n\nQualifications & skills\nExcellent communication skills, both verbal and written in English and Romanian.\nBachelor\'s degree or higher, ideally from a technical institution.\nProficient in creating structured Requirements and Acceptance Criteria that minimize development rework and ensure technical alignment.\nComfortable interviewing clients/people about their behavior and needs\nCapable of interpreting code to perform root cause analysis, validate data integrity, and optimize system integration workflows.\nExpertise in transforming ambiguous stakeholder input into structured, hierarchical documentation\n\nNice to have\nCertification in Business Analysis\nProficiency in using Spanish and/or French and/or German is a plus\n\nOur recruitment process\nWe will use a two-step process for the recruitment of this role:\nA practical exercise\nAn interview with the product team, where we aim to learn more about you and your skills for this role.\n\nCareer development\nShould you be interested in further professional development, we will support you to boost your skills and capabilities. Being a product company, we have a wider breadth of departments and skills that may be attractive to you:\nProduct Management\nProject Management\nAccount Management\n\nWe place efficiency at the core of our business. Our day-to-day efforts contribute to improving the quality of passengers’ travel experience all across the world.\n\nWe foster a values-driven culture; therefore, it is essential that colleagues who join our team abide by and uphold our company values: Assertiveness, Efficiency, Grit, Initiative, Kindness & Collaboration, Knowledge transfer, Openness, Ownership, Responsibility & Accountability, Predictability, Psychological safety, and Transparency.', 100, 'SALVAT', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-24 21:38:08', '2026-05-24 20:24:01', NULL, NULL, 'BACHELOR', 'Licență', NULL, 1);
