(182, NULL, 4, 'Technical Analyst – AI & Marketing Intelligence', 'Yardi', 'Cluj-Napoca', 'HYBRID', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DATA', 'Gradient Boosting', 0.1996, '[{\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0.1996}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0.1515}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0.1344}, {\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 0.1168}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0.0608}, {\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0.041}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Despre job\nWho We Are\nWe are a software development company where people, passion, and technology come together to shape the future of real estate through our own innovative products.\nSince opening our doors in 2010, our Cluj-Napoca office has grown into the second-largest Yardi location worldwide. As part of Yardi Systems, Inc., a global leader in real estate software, founded in 1984, we\'re connected to a network of over 45 offices and 10,000+ colleagues across the globe.\nOur success is driven by a diverse team of more than 1,400 professionals, including software developers, marketers, consultants, data researchers, customer service specialists, and many more. Think you\'d be a great fit? Join #TeamYardi.\n\nYour Impact\nYou see a repetitive task and immediately think about how to automate it. You get excited connecting tools, designing agents, and making AI do the heavy lifting. But you don’t stop at internal hacks: you want to build AI-powered features that real users rely on. If you also happen to love data and can navigate a complex database with ease, we want to talk to you.\nPropertyShark is a leading commercial real estate data platform used by brokers, investors, and researchers across the US. As a Technical Analyst-AI & Marketing Intelligence, you’ll own two complementary missions:\nAI Automation for the Marketing Team. Identify manual workflows across the team and replace them with intelligent automation. Build pipelines, connect data sources and tools, create reusable playbooks, and be the go-to person who translates business problems into AI-powered solutions that improve quality and velocity.\nProduct-Facing AI Features. Design and build AI-powered experiences for PropertyShark’s clients. This includes prototyping AI assistants, AI-assisted search and research workflows, and agentic systems that connect to live data through tool-use architectures and MCP servers. You’ll take these from concept through testing, evaluation, and production-readiness.\nThis hybrid role requires working from the office at least once a week, so please take into account that you should be based in or near Cluj-Napoca.\n\nWhat You\'ll Bring Along\n2+ years in a data-heavy analyst or technical role where you worked with large datasets, built reports, or automated workflows\nBachelor\'s degree in Marketing, Business, Computer Science, or related field is preferred but not required\nHands-on experience designing and deploying AI agents or AI-powered workflows using LLMs (OpenAI, Claude, or similar), including prompt engineering and tool-use / function-calling patterns\nExperience with automation platforms (n8n, Flowise, Zapier, or custom API orchestrations)\nWorking knowledge of Python, enough to build, adapt, and troubleshoot data pipelines, automation scripts, and AI integrations (with or without AI assistance)\nUnderstanding of agentic AI concepts: multi-step reasoning, tool-use architectures, context management, and connecting agents to external data via APIs or MCP servers\nSolid SQL skills for querying large databases\nStrong analytical thinking, attention to detail, and clear communication skills\nNice to have:\nExperience with LLM evaluation, testing, and observability tools (e.g., LangSmith, custom eval frameworks)\nFamiliarity with LangChain, LlamaIndex, CrewAI, or similar agent/orchestration frameworks\nPortfolio of previous AI, automation, or data analysis projects you can walk us through\nBackground in marketing operations or marketing technology\nExperience with data visualization tools (Looker, Tableau, Power BI)\nAdvanced Excel skills (pivot tables, Power Query, data modeling, VBA/macros)\nFamiliarity with real estate data, SEO tools, or product analytics\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\nAI Automation & Workflow Intelligence\nAudit the marketing team’s workflows; identify repetitive, manual processes and design AI-powered replacements: from prompt-based automation to multi-step agent pipelines\nBuild and maintain automations using platforms like n8n, Flowise, or custom API orchestrations, connecting internal tools, CRMs, analytics platforms, and data sources\nDocument every solution into reusable playbooks so the team can adopt, maintain, and extend your work independently\nBe the team’s AI advisor: evaluate new tools, run proof-of-concepts, and help marketers integrate AI into their daily work\nData & Analytics\nBuild and maintain marketing dashboards, KPIs, and analytics reports across website traffic, user behavior, and business metrics\nDig into large real estate datasets using SQL and Python; turn numbers into actionable decisions\nIdentify data-driven opportunities where predictive models or AI features could enhance the platform\nProduct AI & Agentic Systems\nDesign and prototype AI-driven features for the PropertyShark platform: AI assistants, conversational property research tools, AI-assisted workflows for clients\nArchitect agentic AI systems: multi-step agents that reason, call tools, and interact with live real estate data through MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers and API integrations\nBuild evaluation and testing frameworks for AI outputs: define quality metrics, detect hallucinations, run systematic evals and set up logging and observability for production agents\nCollaborate with product and engineering teams to move prototypes from proof-of-concept to reliable, production-grade features\n\nWhat you\'ll enjoy once you become part of the Yardi Romania team:\nA flexible hybrid work setup that blends the best of remote and office life.\nUp to $2,000 per year reimbursed for eligible learning and professional development expenses.\n40 RON/working day meal tickets (taxable according to current legislation).\nUp to 26 vacation days to recharge your energy, based on tenure.\nComprehensive private medical insurance (including dental care, physiotherapy & psychotherapy) for you and your dependents.\nUp to 20 days of EU remote work per year, subject to current policy.\nAnnual salary review to keep it in line with your performance and industry changes.\nThe possibility of a yearly bonus through our profit-sharing program.\nLife insurance for you & global travel insurance for you and your family.\nCurrently granting a fixed monthly Work/Life Stipend for your well-being activities.\nDiscounts at gyms, restaurants, and other service providers.\nAll necessary equipment provided for both home and office setups.\nA modern, central workspace @ The Office in Cluj-Napoca, with an open-air terrace and game rooms to unwind.\nFresh fruit, snacks, and specialty coffee available daily at the office.\nEngaging office events, themed parties, and team buildings.', 77, 'SALVAT', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-24 21:43:17', '2026-05-24 20:24:01', 2, '2+ ani', 'BACHELOR', 'Licență', 0, 1),
(183, NULL, 4, 'Business Analyst - Medical Devices', 'dotLumen', 'România', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BUSINESS', 'Gradient Boosting', 0.5411, '[{\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 0.5411}, {\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0.4589}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Despre job\n300 million people need your skills to change their lives. \nFor thousands of years, blind individuals only had 2 mobility solutions: the guide dog and the white cane. Now, your work can change that. You can contribute to bringing the Glasses for the Blind, the most innovative mobility solution that will empower millions to live a better life, to Europe and beyond. \nThis is for the crazy ones, the ones who believe their work can change the world.\n\nWhat You’ll be doing:\nWork out the finer details of introducing medical devices into various countries around Europe and figure out how the Glasses for the Blind can fit into the specifics of regional insurance systems \nAnalyze reimbursement pathways, government programs and sheltered workshop schemes for assistive technologies across EU markets \nGather lots of data, build insights and contribute heavily go-to market plans\nConduct research on markets, pricing, reimbursement and distribution structures\nIdentify partnership opportunities with distributors and market-entry partners, contribute to our distribution strategy. \nAssist the Business Development team in winning & managing business partnerships, ranging from market-entry partners, technological partners, or marketing partners.\n\nYour skills\nFirst and foremost, curiosity, structure and accountability. What you will be doing is on the cutting edge of what is possible and has never been done before.\nStrong analytical mindset – you love data, dashboards and most of all making sense of chaos\nYou are a top-performing individual with a background or strong interest in Sales and Revenue Ops, Business Analysis\nProcess design and tooling decisions – figure out how to do things better – implement – teach others\nComfortable working with CRM systems and data tools \nYou have the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and interpret data and information with attention to detail and accuracy. Like seriously, you must be obsessed with organization and playing Sherlock. \nGraduate of Law, Economics, or similar academic background.\n\nYour life @.lumen\nYou will be part of the team that changed the world. Your work will ultimately improve the lives of many.\n· Each day is different. There is no monotony here, just great challenges, a creative environment, and fun colleagues.\n· Your work will be used in days, not years.\n· You will work within a small team, complementing each other. \n· You’ll receive a lot of support. \n\nWhat else we offer?\n· Attractive salary (obviously…) \n· Employee Stock Option Program through which employees that bring a significant impact are rewarded with company stock \n· Flexible schedule \n\nWhat’s next?\nOur recruitment process includes 4 steps:\n1. We review your application \n2. The most suited candidates meet us for an informal discussion \n3. Next, we invite the best to join a challenge led by Cornel Amariei\n4. We get to meet the winner for the final interview with Cornel Amariei\n\nAbout .lumen\n.lumen builds Pedestrian Autonomous Driving, first showcased in the Glasses for the Blind.\nThere are over 300 million visually impaired individuals worldwide, and while technology advances, the most commonly used solutions for them—guide dogs and white canes—are thousands of years old. At .lumen, we are changing this paradigm.\n.lumen is a research startup leveraging the most advanced AI, robotics, and neuroscience technologies to empower the blind. This is no easy task, and we are looking for the best in the world to help us achieve it.\nIn just four years, .lumen has become one of the most awarded startups globally. From opening Nvidia GTC in front of millions to winning the Red Dot: Luminary award and becoming the first Romanian company to raise over €9 million from the European Innovation Council (EIC), our journey has been remarkable.\n\nOur work is already in the history books, and our story is still being written. \nCome write it with us. Also, check our video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Im-Gsn5PKG8', 100, 'SALVAT', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-24 21:53:32', '2026-05-24 19:54:47', 0, '0 ani / entry-level', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL),
(188, NULL, 4, 'IBM internship Data Engineer', 'IBM', 'Nespecificat', 'HYBRID', 'INTERNSHIP', NULL, NULL, 'DATA', 'Gradient Boosting', 0.3107, '[{\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0.3107}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0.1305}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0.1158}, {\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 0.1006}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0.0849}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0.0849}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0.0849}, {\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0.0523}, {\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0.0353}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Introduction\n\nA career in IBM Consulting is built on long-term client relationships and close collaboration worldwide. You’ll work with leading companies across industries, helping them shape their hybrid cloud and AI journeys. With support from our strategic partners, robust IBM technology, and Red Hat, you’ll have the tools to drive meaningful change and accelerate client impact. At IBM Consulting, curiosity fuels success. You’ll be encouraged to challenge the norm, explore new ideas, and create innovative solutions that deliver real results. Our culture of growth and empathy focuses on your long-term career development while valuing your unique skills and experiences.\n\nYour Role And Responsibilities\n\nThe internship program is offered for a fixed period of 3 months, with the possibility of extending the collaboration based on performance and business needs. During the recruitment process, you may receive a call from our colleagues on the international team (from a Hungarian or Slovak number). Please answer, as the call is related to your application.\n\nData Engineering Internship consist of development of the Snowflake‑based Data Hub by assisting in the setup and integration of non‑production environments and ensuring alignment with the organization’s infrastructure standards. You will contribute to deployment pipelines and code repositories, and assist in establishing automated CI/CD processes. You will also support the integration of central job control to enable orchestrated ETL/ELT workflows, working closely with infrastructure teams to ensure secure and compliant implementation.\n\nPreferred Education\n\nMaster\'s Degree\n\nRequired Technical And Professional Expertise\n\nBasic understanding of Python programming and SQL.\n\nInterest in data engineering, ETL processes or analytics.\n\nFamiliarity with concepts such as joins, aggregations, filtering, or basic scripting.\n\nProblem-solving mindset and willingness to learn new technologies.\n\nGood communication skills and ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.\n\nCuriosity, initiative, and eagerness to grow technically and professionally.\n\nPreferred Technical And Professional Experience\n\nExposure to PySpark, Pandas, or any data-related projects.\n\nBasic understanding of databases or cloud platforms.\n\nPersonal, academic, or GitHub projects related to Python, data processing, or automation.', 70, 'SALVAT', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-24 22:50:04', '2026-06-03 11:47:58', NULL, NULL, 'MASTER', 'Master', NULL, 1),
(189, NULL, 4, 'Graduate software engineer', 'Bending Spoons', 'Cluj-Napoca', 'REMOTE', 'PART_TIME', NULL, NULL, 'DATA', 'Gradient Boosting', 0.1996, '[{\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0.1996}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0.1515}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0.1344}, {\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 0.1168}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0.0987}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0.0608}, {\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0.041}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Despre job\nAt Bending Spoons, we’re striving to build one of the all-time great companies. A company that serves a huge number of customers. A company where team members grow to their full potential. A company that functions at unparalleled levels of effectiveness and efficiency. A company that creates value for shareowners at an extraordinary rate. And a company that does so while adhering to high ethical standards.\n\nIn pursuit of this objective, we acquire and improve digital businesses, not to sell on, but to own and operate for the long term. The transformations we make are often deep—designed to speed up innovation, benefit customers, and strengthen business performance. Here, hierarchy is minimal and teams are small and talent-dense. We operate established products with the ambition, agility, and urgency of a startup. Across the company, we integrate AI deeply into how we work so that human judgment and machine intelligence reinforce each other.\n\nFor a talented, driven, and collaborative individual, working at Bending Spoons is an opportunity to learn, make an impact, and progress their career at an exceptionally high rate. That’s our promise to such a candidate.\n\nA few examples of your responsibilities\nBuild software that matters. Take real ownership from idea to production, creating systems used by millions and evolving them into products at scale.\nAmplify your impact with AI. Integrate the most powerful AI tools directly into your development workflow—design, implementation, testing, and documentation—to move faster while maintaining high standards for correctness, reliability, and maintainability.\nMaster your toolkit. Work across diverse stacks with end-to-end ownership, choosing the right technologies for each challenge. From monoliths to microservices, gRPC to REST, Kubernetes to Docker, Python to Rust—you’ll apply technologies thoughtfully, focusing on depth and purpose rather than trends.\nSimplify relentlessly. Question every layer of complexity. Improve architectures, pipelines, and codebases to build systems that are simpler, more scalable, and easier to maintain.\n\nWhat we look for\nReasoning ability. Given the necessary knowledge, you can solve complex problems. You think from first principles, and structure your ideas sharply. You resist the influence of biases. You identify and take care of the details that matter.\nDrive. You’re extremely ambitious in everything you do—and your initiative, effort, and tenacity match the intensity of your ambition. You feel deeply responsible for your work. You hold yourself to a high—and rising—bar.\nTeam spirit. You give generously and without the expectation of receiving in return. You support the best idea, not your idea. You\'re always happy to get your hands dirty to help your team. You’re reliable, honest, and transparent.\nProficiency in English. You read, write, and speak proficiently in English.\n\nWhat we offer\nIncredibly talented, entrepreneurial teams. You’ll work in small, result-oriented, autonomous teams alongside some of the brightest people in your field.\nAn exceptional opportunity for growth. We go to great lengths to hire individuals of outstanding potential—then, our priority is to put them in the ideal position to thrive. Spooners in their 20s lead products worth hundreds of millions of dollars. And if you’ve got what it takes, you’ll soon be playing an essential role in major projects, too.\nCompetitive pay and access to equity in the company. Typically, we offer individuals at the start of their career an annual salary of £85,797 in London and €66,065 elsewhere in Europe. For a candidate that we assess as possessing considerable relevant experience, the salary on offer tends to be between £112,189 and £250,512 in London, and €107,837 and €188,848 elsewhere in Europe. Compensation varies by location and expected impact, and grows rapidly as you gain experience and translate it into greater contributions. For individuals who demonstrate exceptional capability, we may offer compensation that extends beyond the usual ranges to reflect their higher expected impact. If you\'re offered a permanent contract, you\'ll also be able receive some of your pay in company equity at a discounted price, thus participating in the value creation we achieve together. If relocating to Italy, you may enjoy a 50% tax cut.\nAll. These. Benefits. Flexible hours, remote working, unlimited backing for learning and training, top-of-the-market health insurance, a rich relocation package, generous parental support, and a yearly retreat to a stunning location. We help each Spooner set up the conditions to do their best work.\nA flexible start date and part-time options. You don\'t need to wait until graduation to apply. We offer flexible start dates and the possibility to begin part-time, transitioning to full-time as you complete your degree. Many Spooners joined before graduating and progressively took on greater responsibility, with arrangements that allowed them to do so without compromising their education.\n\nCommitment & contract\nPermanent or fixed-term. Full-time.\n\nLocation\nMilan (Italy), London (UK), Madrid (Spain), Warsaw (Poland) or remote in selected countries.\n\nThe selection process\nIn our screening process, we prioritize verifiable signals of excellence, regardless of seniority. There are no preferential paths beyond what your application demonstrates, and we evaluate every candidate through the same process. Some people hold back because they feel they lack experience or have an “imperfect” CV. If you like the role and believe you could excel over time, don’t self-reject.\n\nAll applications go through our careers page, which is the only way to be considered. If you pass our screening, you’ll be asked to complete one or more tests. They are challenging, may involve unfamiliar problems, and can take several hours.\n\nWe set the bar high and won’t extend an offer until we’re confident we’ve found the right candidate. This is why a job may remain open for months or be reposted several times.\n\nWe consider all applicants for employment and provide reasonable accommodations for individuals with disabilities—please let us know through this form.\n\nBefore you apply\nIf you’ve applied before but didn\'t receive an offer, we recommend waiting at least one year before applying again.\n\nBending Spoons is a demanding environment. We’re extremely ambitious and we hold ourselves—and one another—to a high standard. While this tends to lead to extraordinary learning, achievement, and career growth, it also requires significant commitment.\n\nTo help you ramp up quickly and set yourself up for success, we recommend spending your first few months working from our Milan office, regardless of your long-term work location. It’s the best way to rapidly absorb our company culture and build trust with your new teammates. We’ll support you with generous travel and accommodation assistance. After that, you’re welcome to work from our offices in Milan or London, or remotely from approved countries—depending on what we agree at the offer stage.\n\nIf the role speaks to you and you’re excited to give your best, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now—we can’t wait to meet you.', 83, 'INTERVIU', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-26 12:35:21', '2026-06-07 21:26:33', 0, NULL, 'BACHELOR', 'Licență', NULL, NULL),
(190, NULL, 4, 'Working Student Data Scientist', 'Bosch', 'Cluj-Napoca', 'HYBRID', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DATA', 'Gradient Boosting', 0.1996, '[{\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0.1996}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0.1515}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0.1344}, {\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 0.1168}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0.0986}, {\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0.0608}, {\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0.041}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Despre job\nAbout Bosch Engineering Center Cluj\n\nSince its establishment in 2013, Bosch Engineering Center Cluj plays an essential role in the current transformation of the mobility sector. Through its extensive expertise in software, hardware & mechanical engineering, reliability engineering, as well as sales planning, the center contributes to the development of innovative products and services based on artificial intelligence (AI) applied in the fields of automated driving, electric and connected mobility. Thanks to the diverse professional and personal development opportunities, flexible working conditions, modern offices and laboratories in Cluj-Napoca, Jucu, Bucharest and Sibiu, we are one of the most desired employers among engineers and IT professionals in Romania.\n\nOur promise to our colleagues is rock-solid: we grow together, we enjoy our work, and inspire each other. Join us and see the difference.\n\nWork LikeABosch\n\n\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are looking for university students that are interested in gaining experience in Data Science.\n\n \n\nAs a Working Student in the Data Science group, you will work with us on creating data-driven products and service development for mobility area. Smart services for mobility are also provided in the context of creating high performance teams working together with an internationally distributed team, in a hybrid working model. Become part of our team and join us in creating state of the art data products.\n\nAs a member of our team you take part in topics such as: \n\nDevelop and apply statistical, data mining, machine learning and AI algorithms;\nCreate data products and services for use cases from different domains of Mobility Area where you will use various data types from images, sensor data, unstructured text to solve real life problems;\nWork with a large variety of data sources: from databases, log files to sensor event streams or images;\nDevelop and maintain the data science solution libraries, data visualizations and analytics results;\nHave active participation and responsibility in each phase of the CRISP-DM cycle.\n\nQualifications\n\nBachelor or master’s studies in progress in Computer Science, Automation, Information Theory, Informatics, Mathematics or comparable fields;\nWorked with: Python, PySpark, SQL;\nBasic knowledge/heard of: Large Language Models, Cloud Computing, Azure, Mongo, SQL, Docker, Pandas, Numpy, Seaborn, etc.;\nContact with version source control (e.g. Git, Bitbucket);\nKnow-how from the following fields: Data mining and Statistical Analysis, Data Visualization, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Data preprocessing;\nYou are genuinely curious to solve real life problems, understand capabilities of new technologies, create useful digital products and services.\nExcellent communication skills in English, both spoken and written are mandatory.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nLikeABosch Benefits:\n\nYour work-life balance is valuable to us, so we offer you:\n\n25 Days of annual leave, because work-life balance is essential to us; \nFlexible working hours and if you want to work from somewhere else than the office, our Home Office program helps you do that for up to  70% of your working time/month.\nYour health and well-being is important to us, so we have you covered:\n\nMedical subscription;\nAccident insurance;\nSport activities and well-being initiatives.\nWe believe in a Life-Long Learning approach, so you can take advantage of:\n\nTechnical and soft skills trainings;\nAccess to e-learning platforms;\nLocal and Global career development programs;\nOpportunity to attend conferences;\nBookster subscription.\nYou will be part of a product company. You will contribute to developing end-to-end products that are delivered to Global OEMs.\n\nOn top of these, we are offering:\n\nA monthly budget which can be used for several different services on an online benefit platform;\nAnnual bonus;\nLunch discounts.\nReady to work LikeABosch?\n\nWe live by our values, have an open feedback culture and there is plenty of room for innovative ideas. All because a team is only as valuable as its members.', 50, 'APLICAT', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-03 14:47:14', '2026-06-07 21:26:33', NULL, NULL, 'MASTER', 'Master', NULL, 0),
(191, NULL, 4, 'Junior Full Stack Developer', 'TechNova Solutions', 'Nespecificat', 'HYBRID', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FULLSTACK', 'Gradient Boosting', 0.7510, '[{\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0.751}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0.2489}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0.0001}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Companie fictivă\n\nTechNova Solutions\n\nDescriere:\n\nTechNova Solutions este o companie software specializată în dezvoltarea de aplicații web și soluții digitale pentru companii din domeniul financiar și al comerțului electronic. Compania dezvoltă produse utilizând tehnologii moderne și încurajează învățarea continuă și dezvoltarea profesională a angajaților.\n\n⸻\n\nAnunț de job fictiv\n\nTechNova Solutions își extinde echipa și caută un Junior Full Stack Developer pasionat de dezvoltarea aplicațiilor web moderne.\n\nResponsabilități:\n\n* Dezvoltarea și întreținerea aplicațiilor web;\n* Implementarea componentelor frontend utilizând React;\n* Dezvoltarea serviciilor backend folosind Node.js și Express;\n* Integrarea și optimizarea bazelor de date MySQL;\n* Participarea la testarea și documentarea aplicațiilor;\n* Colaborarea cu membrii echipei în cadrul proiectelor software.\n\nCerințe:\n\n* Cunoștințe de JavaScript;\n* Experiență cu React;\n* Cunoștințe Node.js și Express;\n* Baze de date relaționale (MySQL);\n* HTML și CSS;\n* Git și GitHub;\n* Înțelegerea principiilor REST API;\n* Cunoștințe de bază despre autentificare JWT;\n* Abilități de rezolvare a problemelor și lucru în echipă.\n\nReprezintă un avantaj:\n\n* Python;\n* Machine Learning;\n* Docker;\n* TypeScript;\n* Experiență cu metodologii Agile.\n\nBeneficii:\n\n* Program flexibil;\n* Mentorat tehnic;\n* Buget anual pentru cursuri și certificări;\n* Posibilitatea de lucru hibrid;\n* Participare la proiecte reale de dezvoltare software.', 100, 'SALVAT', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-07 23:56:44', '2026-06-07 21:26:42', 0, '0 ani / entry-level', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL),
(192, NULL, 4, 'IT Support Working Student', 'BMW TechWorks Romania', 'Nespecificat', NULL, 'INTERNSHIP', NULL, NULL, 'PM', 'Gradient Boosting', 0.8788, '[{\"category\": \"PM\", \"probability\": 0.8788}, {\"category\": \"DATA\", \"probability\": 0.0369}, {\"category\": \"BACKEND\", \"probability\": 0.0157}, {\"category\": \"FRONTEND\", \"probability\": 0.0157}, {\"category\": \"BUSINESS\", \"probability\": 0.0136}, {\"category\": \"AI_ML\", \"probability\": 0.0115}, {\"category\": \"BI\", \"probability\": 0.0115}, {\"category\": \"QA\", \"probability\": 0.0115}, {\"category\": \"FULLSTACK\", \"probability\": 0.0048}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Despre job\nWho We Are\n\nEverything at BMW TechWorks begins with passion. It transforms a job into a calling. It motivates us to continually reinvent mobility and bring new ideas to life and onto the roads. Passion for collaborative projects turns a team into a strong unit where every viewpoint is appreciated.\n\nWhatever You Aspire To, At BMW TechWorks We Live And Breathe Software And We Offer a Wide Variety Of Departments And Fields Where You Can Share Your Professional Passion With Us. By Delivering Software All The Way From The Idea To The Final Product, We Lead BMW Into The Future Of Digitalization And Mobility. And This Also Means\n\nWe search for excellence \nWe get involved \nWe keep it simple \nWe share trust \n\nJoin BMW TechWorks on our journey of innovation and excellence as we redefine the future of motion, one product at a time. Our engineers are vital to the innovation and digitalization of BMW Group\'s driving machines, production, sales and banking processes, and you could be part of our evolving teams.\n\nWhat Awaits You\n\nDuring this 6-month internship, you will be part of the IT Support team and contribute to daily operational activities, gaining hands-on experience with enterprise IT systems and end-user support.\n\nMain Responsibilities\n\nProvide first-level technical support (L1) for hardware, software, and network-related issues\nAssist users with Microsoft 365 services (Outlook, Teams, OneDrive, SharePoint)\nSupport user account management tasks (password resets, access requests, group memberships) in Entra ID (Azure AD)\nHelp with device setup and configuration (Windows laptops, MacBooks, mobile devices)\nAssist in troubleshooting common IT issues (connectivity, applications, printing, etc.)\nSupport software installation and updates according to company standards\nContribute to IT asset management (inventory tracking, device lifecycle support)\nAssist with Intune-related activities (basic device enrollment, policy checks, compliance status)\nDocument incidents, solutions, and internal procedures in the ticketing system\nCollaborate with senior IT team members on ongoing projects and improvements\nParticipation in IT security and compliance initiatives (endpoint protection, access control)\nBasic scripting or automation tasks (PowerShell – optional)\nSupporting rollout of IT policies or tools (e.g., deployment via Intune)\nAssisting in documentation creation (guides, internal knowledge base)\n\nWhat Should You Bring Along\n\nWe are looking for a motivated candidate eager to learn and grow in an IT support environment.\n\nMandatory Requirements\n\nUniversity Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or a related field (or currently enrolled)\n0–1 year of experience (internship experience or academic projects in IT is a plus)\nBasic understanding of operating systems (Windows and/or macOS)\nBasic knowledge of networking concepts (IP, DNS, connectivity troubleshooting)\nFamiliarity with Microsoft 365 is a plus\nExcellent English verbal and written skills\nStrong communication and customer-oriented mindset\nWillingness to learn and adapt in a fast-paced environment\n\nNice To Have\n\nGerman communication skills will be a plus\nBasic knowledge of Entra ID / Active Directory\nExposure to Intune / device management tools\nBasic scripting knowledge (PowerShell)\nUnderstanding of IT security basics\n\nWhat do we offer?\n\nChallenging projects with which we are shaping the mobility of tomorrow. \nGreat team spirit within an international team \nState-of-the-art global IT landscape and processes \n100% implementation of the Agile Working Model methodology \nWide range of personal & professional development opportunities \nHigh level of job security \nWork-Life-Balance and flexible working hours. \nDynamic and highly-motivating work environment', 60, 'SALVAT', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-26 18:34:20', '2026-06-26 15:34:20', 0, '0-1 ani', 'BACHELOR', 'Licență', 1, 1);
